name: Waroeng Spesial Sambal "SS" Batu Bulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: good food, taste good, so spicy but I love it, very recommended
review 2:
This waroeng is a good place to hang with your buddies if you enjoy hot and spicy chili mix with Indonesian style fried chicken. Unfortunately, the meat might not be what you expect, it‚Äôs rather tough and dry.

They are rather packed for a dinner, and people come and go while we were eating, so it‚Äôs definitely popular. The sambal is their main point though, so it looks like I‚Äôm not the target market.
review 3:
They serve Indonesian food and various sambal or spices

Lunch time is very crowded your order will be take long

Affordable price
Food is tasty, they offer fried or grill
Spacious parking lot
review 4:
Calling out all spicy lovers to go to this restaurant!!
All food taste good with affordable price. The parking area wasn't that large but quite enough for 20 motorbikes and maybe 2 cars. They have many variants of sambal you can try it one by one. I really love their "sambal terasi matang" and "sambal bajak". Payment method is available for cash and debit-cardüëç
review 5: Offers halal food known to locals here . Was brought by our local driver and this place did not disappoint. Dishes were cooked on the spot and tasted really really good! Portion are small but prove is reasonable . Rice would be charged as per pax but can be refillable . Great hidden gem!

name: Batubulan
address: 97P4+7RW, Batubulan, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: Photograph isn‚Äôt allowed . Only 1-2 hand  weaver. A big show room of art and craft items specifically balis style cloths and bed sheets
review 2: The driver from kabinawa Bali tours is amazing great customer service and the best tour guide in Bali

name: Kecak Dance Batubulan
address: Jl. Smki No.25, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: The fire dance in Bali is an enchanting and mesmerizing experience. The skillful dancers, with their dynamic movements and the dramatic play of flames, create a captivating spectacle. It's a vibrant expression of Balinese culture and a must-see for anyone visiting the island..
review 2:
I watched the Barong Dance in the morning (08.30 - 09.30 WITA/GMT +8), spacious space to watch Barong Dance. They provide ID-EN-CN flyers about the story of Barong Dance.

Different prices for locals and foreigners.
review 3: Loved the morning performance. The written synopsis of the play was super helpful, meaning we knew just what the story was about. The Barong in particular was mesmerizing - I couldn't tear my eyes away! Musicians played beautifully too.
review 4: Absolutely an interesting performance, The Barong and Keris dance live performance was so amazing to watched while you on the way to ubud tour, wasn't nor complete if we not watching this balinesse culture while you visiting Bali island definitely amazing dance, affordable ticket entrance, it is took time approximetely an hour only.
review 5: Really enjoyed the cultural dancing. Highly recommend.

name: Tari Barong Dan Keris Batubulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan No.295X, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: This one place you can enjoy traditional bali dance, one of famous is Barong dance. Barong is mythologycal animal from Bali and symbol of righteousness and justice. The show take about 45 minutes and you will have a stories script with some language choice like english, japan, china, france etc.. but all performance will perform in Balinese language, ya sometimes maybe the artist will speak in english but not many, hopefully they can upgrade the show in english and have any screen to show the plot of stories in english text, it's hard to understand the performance because we can't understand the language and sometimes it feel boring. But i'm apriciate with all artist and give a spectacular performance for all guest :)
review 2: one of the Balinese dances which contains many interesting stories, including the story about good versus evil... and there are also funny stories... worth watching...
review 3: Very nice place with traditional Bali style dance
review 4: Best tasting satay we had in Bali. Not the biggest, but very flavoursome.
review 5: On the way right to , we are stopped there.. take a look

name: KALAMANSI - BALINESE - INDONESIAN RESTAURANT
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan No.99, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Spacious restaurant, not many visitors.
It was only me and my husband enjoying their meals, coffee, and cake. All of our orders were top notch. Price also fair. Hence, quiet surprise they‚Äôre empty of customers. Located next to main road, close to the Bali Bird Park. Worth a try.
review 2: Very good food at good prices especially batagor dumplings and amazing lychee and lemon iced tea, pleasant service
review 3:
Stopped by here for lunch in between the bird park and the butterfly park. Food was quite good, though not super fantastic. Enjoyed the nasi goreng and mie goreng. Ayam panggang was decent but not the best. I thought my iced latte was too watered down. Pumpkin soup was too much pumpkin and not enough cream. Desserts wise, the oreo cheesecake had too much cream and not enough oreo, and the opera was a tad dry though the taste is quite good.

Atmosphere is not bad, quite a big place with lots of space, and it wasn't busy on a late Saturday lunch.
review 4: Tasty nasi goreng and mie goreng, pizza was great too and so was beef burger. Fries portion too small. Ayam pangang manis was the least impressive along with pumpkin soup which was too viscous and thick. Juices and iced teas were fresh and cooling. Oreo cheesecake and classic opera were too dense, didn't enjoy them as much. Service was good, they serve complimentary cold water, place was clean and spacious, toilets are indoors and adequate. Overall a nice place to stop by for lunch after visiting Bali Bird Park. Highly recommend.
review 5:
Loved the food. The menu is very good. We tried nasi goreng seafood, nasi goreng kembing, Gerang Asem Iga, Gulai Nangka, teriyaki salmon and chicken burger. All were so tasty. Wanted to try papaya salad too. Next time may be. Ice milk coffee was good. Nice decent brownie too. Coffee was same as melbourne.
Very affordable price with out the worry about hygiene as I have young kids with me.
Very nice environment.
We saw the bird park and reptile park and this resturant is 7 min from there.
The staff we so welcoming and helpful.
Overall exceeded expectation.

name: Warung Sate Babi Buk Nyoman
address: 97Q3+H7P, Batubulan, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: For just 15,000 IDR, I enjoyed a delightful meal of white rice paired with pork satay. It was not only delicious but also offered great value for the money.
review 2: We ordered babi sate. The lady said 9k without rice and 15k with rice. When we went to pay, she said everything is 15 K. Such a scammer
review 3: Good pork satay. Taste so yummy and juicy. The price is very cheap only 15k for 1 plate full of pork satay with rice. They also sell some pork skin cracker. I eat 5 portion satay and rice with a lot of pork skin cracker and 4 soft drink only 90k rupiah. Very reccomended for people who want come to ubud and monkey forest to visit this place and have a great lunch
review 4: One of the best pork satay I‚Äôve eaten in Bali, if you are heading to Ubud from Sanur or Denpasar you can easily spot this humble sate joint. The satay spices is nice, you can either eat the satay with nasi sela (rice with yam chunks) or with tipat (ketupat or steamed shaped rice).
review 5: They serve traditional pork satay ala Bali

name: Warung Babi Guling Mika
address: 97Q3+983, Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: It's a family run business which makes the best of the pork. There are many places in Bali which serve this dish but this place has the best. Don't hesitate to try their spicy sambol and fried chicken feet
review 2: I think this is the most authentic Nasi Babi Guling (Roasted Pork with Rice) . Worth the price and the taste really good. You will like it especially if you like food with strong herbs. Served with 'lawar', satay, and pork crackling. They also serve a soup too (i don't really know what's inside but i think it's like some parts of coconut). I recommend this place.
review 3: They have different prices for local 1 set cost 35k. For anyone not Balinese eventho indonesian would be charged with 50k for standard portiona and 60k for complete portion, would suggest just order take away 20-25k/portion.
review 4: One of the best local original taste babi guling in Bali. The place is located roadside on the way to Ubud. Making it a good stopover during your journey. Parking is plenty just on the side of the road. The first thing you see when you enter the restaurant is the Babi Guling displayed on the counter, brings confidence that such a small stall can finish a pig a day. The meat is juicy and crispy, the soup is tasty, and the urap balances everything. Would recommend the restaurant for sure!
review 5: It's a small warung. I am just passing through and saw the warung is so crowded, then I am stopping by. The Nasi Babi Guling is cheap and the taste is ok. Recommended to try.

name: Watuluna Guest House
address: Jl. Sapu Jagad No.13, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: Got an entire loft room for an unbelievable price. The host Bagus is easygoing and has lots of dogs. Dont go if you are scared of small dogs.
review 2: Real-life recommend this place. It has everything you need and it's really chilled. The owner and the staff are the best part, super friendly and will help you out whatever is that you need. They pick you up in the airport and take you to exchange money, buy your things and all the basic arrival needs. Wifi unfortunately isn't good and water pressure also not ideal. Still, would recommend specially if it's your first time in Bali. Oh they also have a scooter to lend you and are happy to give you some driving lessons.
review 3: Great place to stay in Batubulan, Gus will take care of you! Easy access to Sanur and Ubud while still living in a fairly traditional Balinese village area where you can experience the real Bali. Rent a bike from Gus and explore the area, the locals are really friendly and there are traditional markets, silver stores, Kecak and Barong dances, and other great activities nearby.
review 4:
Such a treasure!

The owner was friendly! There's a lot of dogs and I'd love it! üíï

Homey and comfy place! 10000% recommended kalo pusing dengan hiruk pikuk kota.
review 5: I stayed 1 month! Super friendly family, the place was great! Not touristic place, quiet, easy to get Ubud! Owner helped me a lot!! Definitely I will stay here again!!! ;)

review 1: The most delicious Mie Godog or Noodle soup I ever ate. It is cooked in ‚ÄúAnglo‚Äù a traditional stove made from clay, and it uses charcoal. The charcoal smoke gives a unique taste to the food. Mie Godog is originated from Java - Yogyakarta area, and it is famous for most delicious Indonesian cuisine. Other than noodle soup, they also sells fried noodle, fried rice, etc. I am so happy that I find this place on my way from Ubud to Kuta. I might say this is the best Mie Godog in Bali with very affordable price, awesome
review 2:
It was just a try and error kind of thing. If it‚Äôs good, finish the food. If it is bad, let‚Äôs find another. Surprisingly, it‚Äôs good and we ended ordering another plate. For an 18K rupiah tasty noodle, cooked on hot charcoal, and generous portion, this one definitely should not be missed.
Location: exactly across SS Batubulan

name: Cwie Mie Malang Batubulan
address: 97P3+MF3, Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
When travelling to Bali, it's good to try an authentic Javanese food.

To be frank, I haven't tasted Cwie Mie before, but this place served a nice flavorish Cwie Mie and am sure the taste is not far from Cwie Mie served in Malang as the owner herself is preparing the meal.

The place is reasonably small, but it's clean and comfortable. Car parking may have been a small issue as this place is situated just by the street.

Price wise is very affordable and worth every penny.

Payment can be made by cash and Qris.
review 2:
Best Cwie Mie I ever had.. The soup so fresh, noodles delicious & combine taste very good.. Make me smile every time I eat.. Regular customer.. And now they have a delivery order, if near Batu Bulan area, minimum order 100K.. Naiissss..
Suwun Mba..
review 3: Best noodles i had so far in Bali. If you're vegetarian it's no problem because you can order Cwie Mie Ayam Jamur and explains, that you don't need the chicken. She also understand English :)
review 4: Nice place, clean and comfy. Most importantly the noodle is yummy and tasty.
review 5: Finally found this incomparable cwie mie in Bali! It was taste as close as original cwie mie from Malang. Their mie was homemade and crafted by the owner as well. Hope this business will grow and succeed.
